1
00:01:43,280 --> 00:01:44,160
Sir,

2
00:01:44,960 --> 00:01:45,920
take care.

3
00:01:55,320 --> 00:01:56,320
I'm going.

4
00:02:20,600 --> 00:02:22,200
Why are you in such a hurry?

5
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:59,120
Wait.

6
00:02:59,840 --> 00:03:02,240
From what I remember, you never left.

7
00:03:04,040 --> 00:03:06,240
Sir, you must be mistaken.

8
00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:08,760
I've been teaching
in Beijing this whole time.

9
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:12,520
Officer He.

10
00:03:14,560 --> 00:03:15,520
It's really you.

11
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:18,360
Xiaohe, right?

12
00:03:20,720 --> 00:03:21,680
You don't recognize me?

13
00:03:22,960 --> 00:03:24,960
It's me. Qian Daqun.

14
00:03:25,040 --> 00:03:26,880
I used to be the property manager
at Yuanlongli.

15
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:28,840
Now I'm just doing alright.

16
00:03:28,920 --> 00:03:32,040
I'm a deputy manager
for the new developer there.

17
00:03:32,760 --> 00:03:35,160
I'm handling Yuanlongli's
relocation project.

18
00:03:35,760 --> 00:03:36,600
What a coincidence.

19
00:03:37,600 --> 00:03:38,640
Ran's back.

20
00:03:38,720 --> 00:03:40,280
He's back too.

21
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:41,920
Who?

22
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:43,760
Mr. Qian, you must be busy.

23
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:45,480
We won't hold you up.

24
00:03:45,560 --> 00:03:46,680
What do you mean by who?

25
00:03:46,760 --> 00:03:48,320
My apprentice, Ran Fangxu.

26
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:49,480
You don't know him?

27
00:03:50,320 --> 00:03:51,600
Isn't Ran Fangxu already dead?

28
00:03:53,160 --> 00:03:54,400
What are you on about?

29
00:03:54,480 --> 00:03:55,720
Have you lost your mind?

30
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:57,240
He's standing right here.

31
00:03:57,840 --> 00:03:59,200
What kind of nonsense is that?

32
00:03:59,720 --> 00:04:03,520
I get it. Officer He,
you're messing with me, right?

33
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:06,040
It's broad daylight.
You're not scaring me.

34
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:09,280
Still, Officer Ran passed away so young.

35
00:04:09,360 --> 00:04:11,280
It's a real shame.

36
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:13,800
Are you blind? Ran's right…

37
00:04:13,880 --> 00:04:14,720
WEIYANG STATION

38
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:18,440
Ran?

39
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:21,880
Ran Fangxu?

40
00:04:21,959 --> 00:04:23,480
He was here.

41
00:04:24,920 --> 00:04:27,080
What's wrong with him? Has he gone senile?

42
00:04:27,160 --> 00:04:30,000
When Officer Ran died, it was brutal.
Even I know about that.

43
00:04:30,080 --> 00:04:31,120
- Stop talking.
- How could he not know?

44
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:32,960
What did you say? Shut your trap!

45
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:33,960
- Dad.
- Officer He.

46
00:04:34,040 --> 00:04:35,520
- What did you just say?
- Stop!

47
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:37,160
Let's not argue with him. Mr. Qian.

48
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:38,520
You should go.

49
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:40,560
- Dad.
- He must be senile.

50
00:04:41,400 --> 00:04:43,160
He Xiaohe, what's wrong with you?

51
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:45,120
He kept saying Mr. Ran was dead.

52
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:46,240
Didn't you hear him?

53
00:04:46,320 --> 00:04:47,760
You should've backed me up
and shut him down.

54
00:04:47,840 --> 00:04:48,880
We should beat him up.

55
00:04:48,960 --> 00:04:50,000
Ran Fangxu.

56
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:53,200
Where are you? Ran Fangxu,

57
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:55,440
- come out.
- Dad.

58
00:04:55,520 --> 00:04:56,840
I'll say it one more time. Stop hiding.

59
00:04:56,920 --> 00:04:58,040
- Dad, listen to me.
- Let go.

60
00:04:58,720 --> 00:05:01,120
Ran Fangxu! Get out here!

61
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:02,080
Dad.

62
00:05:02,160 --> 00:05:03,200
Don't stop me.

63
00:05:03,280 --> 00:05:05,640
I'm going to the station right now
to pull the surveillance footage.

64
00:05:05,720 --> 00:05:07,480
I'll find out where he's hiding.

65
00:05:07,560 --> 00:05:09,720
Let go. Ran Fangxu!

66
00:05:09,800 --> 00:05:10,720
Get out here!

67
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:12,600
- Dad.
- What are you doing?

68
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:14,360
Let go.

69
00:05:14,440 --> 00:05:15,440
What are you doing?

70
00:05:15,960 --> 00:05:17,240
Ran Fangxu!

71
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:18,800
Come out, Ran Fangxu!

72
00:05:18,880 --> 00:05:20,360
Where are you hiding, rascal?

73
00:05:20,440 --> 00:05:21,520
Get out here!

74
00:05:22,840 --> 00:05:25,920
- Did you hear me?
- Mr. Ran is already dead.

75
00:05:29,960 --> 00:05:31,320
What… What did you say?

76
00:05:37,520 --> 00:05:38,400
Mr. Ran has been dead.

77
00:05:42,760 --> 00:05:44,360
For twelve years.

78
00:05:54,360 --> 00:05:56,520
Young man, have you seen Ran?

79
00:05:56,600 --> 00:05:58,440
Ran Fangxu's holed up in the archives.

80
00:05:59,240 --> 00:06:01,000
He won't pick up his phone.

81
00:06:01,080 --> 00:06:02,240
Slacker.

82
00:06:02,840 --> 00:06:04,200
This is He.

83
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:12,040
- Sir.
- What is that?

84
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:16,520
Don't waste my time.

85
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:17,720
Get out of the car.

86
00:06:18,840 --> 00:06:20,000
Out now.

87
00:06:20,760 --> 00:06:24,360
Something's wrong with this place.

88
00:06:24,440 --> 00:06:28,880
Let go. I want to know
how I end up on that wall.

89
00:06:33,520 --> 00:06:34,760
Easy, easy.

90
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:37,560
Ran!

91
00:06:39,160 --> 00:06:40,120
Ran!

92
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:43,800
Ran!

93
00:06:45,760 --> 00:06:47,520
Hurry up.

94
00:06:48,920 --> 00:06:50,160
You're so clumsy.

95
00:07:00,440 --> 00:07:02,040
Stop playing dumb.

96
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:04,480
Mr. He,

97
00:07:05,520 --> 00:07:08,200
it's time to let go.

98
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:09,920
Dad.

99
00:07:10,440 --> 00:07:11,920
Don't dwell on the past.

100
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:15,880
<i>Once we join hands, we are unstoppable.</i>

101
00:07:16,480 --> 00:07:18,600
Sir, just let it go.

102
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:21,320
It's not worth spending your whole life
chasing one case.

103
00:07:21,920 --> 00:07:24,840
<i>If you hadn't insisted on digging into it,</i>

104
00:07:24,920 --> 00:07:27,440
<i>who knows how many more lives</i>
<i>this cursed building would've taken?</i>

105
00:07:29,520 --> 00:07:30,440
He.

106
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:35,440
Just let Ran go.

107
00:07:35,520 --> 00:07:39,560
<i>As your mentor, I'm ordering you</i>
<i>to stay in Weiyang.</i>

108
00:08:10,840 --> 00:08:14,360
<i>Sir, did you bring me here</i>
<i>to look for the kid?</i>

109
00:08:14,440 --> 00:08:15,760
<i>Or for something else?</i>

110
00:08:15,840 --> 00:08:17,600
<i>Why do you keep coming back to Yuanlongli?</i>

111
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:19,680
<i>I can't keep an eye on him,</i>
<i>restrain him, or stop him.</i>

112
00:08:19,760 --> 00:08:22,120
<i>Sir, stop going to Yuanlongli.</i>

113
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:24,080
<i>You're not to touch</i>
<i>the Yuanlongli case again.</i>

114
00:08:24,160 --> 00:08:25,440
<i>And you're not to go back there either.</i>

115
00:08:25,520 --> 00:08:28,240
<i>You've brought me here again and again.</i>
<i>What exactly are you trying to do?</i>

116
00:08:28,320 --> 00:08:29,160
<i>Not even once more.</i>

117
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:31,320
<i>You just want to keep me in Weiyang</i>

118
00:08:31,400 --> 00:08:32,960
<i>and pull me back into the case</i>
<i>from 18 years ago, don't you?</i>

119
00:08:33,039 --> 00:08:34,400
- <i>And then what?</i>
- <i>Then,</i>

120
00:08:34,480 --> 00:08:37,320
<i>he stays in Weiyang and returns</i>
<i>to the Criminal Department.</i>

121
00:08:38,120 --> 00:08:39,799
<i>Sir, stop going to Yuanlongli.</i>

122
00:08:39,880 --> 00:08:41,720
- <i>Just let Ran go.</i>
- <i>Stop dwelling on the past.</i>

123
00:08:41,799 --> 00:08:43,360
<i>It's time to let go.</i>

124
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:45,360
- <i>Stop going back there.</i>
- <i>Stop dwelling on the past.</i>

125
00:08:45,440 --> 00:08:47,160
<i>Sir, just let it go.</i>

126
00:08:47,240 --> 00:08:48,600
<i>I can't.</i>

127
00:08:54,560 --> 00:08:56,920
<i>Sir, I'm going.</i>

128
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:58,160
<i>Take care.</i>

129
00:08:58,840 --> 00:09:00,040
<i>Dad!</i>

130
00:09:01,640 --> 00:09:06,840
NO. 1 PEOPLE'S HOSPITAL

131
00:09:20,240 --> 00:09:22,400
CARDIOLOGY

132
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:27,520
Xiaohe.

133
00:09:29,120 --> 00:09:29,840
Xiaohe.

134
00:09:34,520 --> 00:09:37,880
Why is Mr. He's episode
taking so long this time?

135
00:09:37,960 --> 00:09:39,240
He's even been hospitalized.

136
00:09:39,320 --> 00:09:41,760
He ran into a real case
at Yuanlongli this time.

137
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:43,840
A real case?

138
00:09:47,480 --> 00:09:51,200
These past two years,
every time he thought he saw Mr. Ran,

139
00:09:51,280 --> 00:09:52,760
he'd drag him back
to Yuanlongli to investigate.

140
00:09:53,440 --> 00:09:54,760
I couldn't stop him.

141
00:09:55,280 --> 00:09:57,200
So I worked with everyone.

142
00:09:57,880 --> 00:10:00,000
We staged a fake missing child case
to keep him occupied.

143
00:10:00,720 --> 00:10:03,240
Ms. Feng, Ma Qiang, and Li Tieling.

144
00:10:03,320 --> 00:10:04,640
They all helped me.

145
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:06,360
Once the child was found,

146
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:08,480
we'd take Mr. Ran
to the train station and send him off.

147
00:10:08,560 --> 00:10:10,320
And my dad would snap out of it.

148
00:10:13,480 --> 00:10:15,680
We didn't expect
there to actually be a missing child

149
00:10:15,760 --> 00:10:17,680
in Yuanlongli this time.

150
00:10:18,320 --> 00:10:19,640
Things got out of our hands.

151
00:10:20,840 --> 00:10:24,880
At the station just now, Qian Dajun
insisted on saying Mr. Ran had already…

152
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:32,160
Qian Dajun, seriously?

153
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:33,880
Does he think before he speaks?

154
00:10:34,720 --> 00:10:36,440
Wasted everyone's time.

155
00:10:38,040 --> 00:10:39,720
The patient's awake. You can go in now.

156
00:10:42,560 --> 00:10:43,600
Dad,

157
00:10:44,280 --> 00:10:45,520
are you feeling any better?

158
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:49,640
Mr. He, I'm Qiao.

159
00:10:50,280 --> 00:10:51,720
Are you alright?

160
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:54,320
Mr. He, I'm Zhao Jie.

161
00:10:54,400 --> 00:10:56,120
The team is here to visit you.

162
00:11:07,640 --> 00:11:09,080
He Yuanhang, are you clear-headed or not?

163
00:11:09,160 --> 00:11:10,000
Answer us.

164
00:11:12,120 --> 00:11:13,160
He,

165
00:11:13,920 --> 00:11:15,960
Captain Ran just called.

166
00:11:16,040 --> 00:11:17,520
He's arrived in Beijing.

167
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:18,840
He told you not to worry.

168
00:11:18,920 --> 00:11:20,160
Yeah.

169
00:11:20,240 --> 00:11:21,840
Captain Ran heard you were hospitalized.

170
00:11:21,920 --> 00:11:22,960
He was worried sick.

171
00:11:23,040 --> 00:11:24,400
- He asked me to--
- Enough.

172
00:11:27,240 --> 00:11:28,440
I remember everything now.

173
00:11:29,720 --> 00:11:30,600
Ran

174
00:11:31,440 --> 00:11:32,720
is gone.

175
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:45,600
The whole team has been going
along with this for over two years.

176
00:11:45,680 --> 00:11:49,520
If it flares up again, no one can take it.

177
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:53,280
Xiaohe.

178
00:11:55,640 --> 00:11:58,640
In the first few years
after Captain Ran passed away,

179
00:11:59,440 --> 00:12:00,360
I used to dream about him all the time.

180
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:05,960
Everyone on the force
who knew him missed him.

181
00:12:07,280 --> 00:12:08,320
Right.

182
00:12:08,400 --> 00:12:10,960
Every time we hit a tough case, we think,

183
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:12,800
if only Captain Ran were still here.

184
00:12:12,880 --> 00:12:15,480
But he's passed away for many years.

185
00:12:15,560 --> 00:12:19,560
He wouldn't want us
to sigh over him every day.

186
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:21,440
It's meaningless.

187
00:12:24,640 --> 00:12:26,640
Go back and talk to Mr. He.

188
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:28,200
He needs to move on.

189
00:12:45,720 --> 00:12:46,840
Xiaohe.

190
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:53,360
I know a really good therapist.

191
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:55,800
Take Mr. He to see him when you have time.

192
00:12:55,880 --> 00:12:58,000
TONG YUNKAI, PSYCHOLOGIST

193
00:13:19,720 --> 00:13:21,200
GET RICH

194
00:15:52,120 --> 00:15:54,280
<i>The Japan-Korea FIFA World Cup</i>
<i>is about to begin.</i>

195
00:15:54,360 --> 00:15:56,200
<i>China, making its first-ever</i>
<i>World Cup appearance,</i>

196
00:15:56,280 --> 00:16:00,360
<i>has been drawn into Group C</i>
<i>with Brazil, Turkey, and Costa Rica.</i>

197
00:16:00,440 --> 00:16:04,120
<i>Let us look forward to a strong showing</i>
<i>from our national team.</i>

198
00:16:08,560 --> 00:16:12,520
WE ADVANCED
2002 KOREA-JAPAN FIFA WORLD CUP

199
00:16:16,160 --> 00:16:20,080
REFORM FOR GROWTH

200
00:16:20,160 --> 00:16:21,520
You're here, Officer He.

201
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:26,680
Check the tire pressure. Top it up.

202
00:16:27,880 --> 00:16:29,840
You've been driving this junk for years.

203
00:16:29,920 --> 00:16:31,800
You're a deputy station chief now.

204
00:16:31,880 --> 00:16:34,000
Why won't you get a better car? Right?

205
00:16:34,080 --> 00:16:35,440
I don't have money.

206
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:37,480
My daughter just started middle school.

207
00:16:37,560 --> 00:16:39,000
Everything costs money.

208
00:16:40,320 --> 00:16:41,480
Officer He,

209
00:16:41,560 --> 00:16:43,120
you and your wife have…

210
00:16:45,240 --> 00:16:47,480
Don't even start.

211
00:16:47,560 --> 00:16:48,680
Hurry up. I have to fetch my girl.

212
00:16:49,320 --> 00:16:52,560
<i>‪They pass the ball like this…</i>
<i>‪Team China's special…</i>

213
00:16:52,640 --> 00:16:57,480
Pay up! Pay up! Pay up!

214
00:16:57,560 --> 00:16:59,360
QINGSONG CEMENT FACTORY, WEIYANG CITY

215
00:16:59,440 --> 00:17:02,400
SAFETY ABOVE ALL

216
00:17:02,480 --> 00:17:04,520
QINGSONG CEMENT FACTORY

217
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:06,520
What's going on here?

218
00:17:07,079 --> 00:17:08,040
They're demanding unpaid wages.

219
00:17:08,560 --> 00:17:09,720
Nothing new.

220
00:17:09,800 --> 00:17:10,560
PAY UP

221
00:17:11,680 --> 00:17:13,319
Since Wu became the factory director,

222
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:15,599
business has gone downhill.

223
00:17:16,440 --> 00:17:17,760
It shut down last month.

224
00:17:19,280 --> 00:17:20,760
He owes the workers a year's pay.

225
00:17:20,839 --> 00:17:22,599
- Where's Wu Shanlong?
- He's hiding.

226
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:25,760
Anywhere there are women,
that's where he'll be.

227
00:17:27,040 --> 00:17:28,200
It's done.

228
00:17:28,280 --> 00:17:31,440
- Pay up!
- Pay up!

229
00:17:31,520 --> 00:17:36,800
SALARY, PAY UP

230
00:17:36,880 --> 00:17:39,880
- Pay up!
- Pay up!

231
00:17:39,960 --> 00:17:42,480
WU SHANLONG

232
00:17:49,800 --> 00:17:53,760
Senior, the problem with this case
is that the scene was washed clean

233
00:17:53,840 --> 00:17:54,840
by last night's heavy rain.

234
00:17:54,920 --> 00:17:56,960
No weapon or usable evidence
has been found.

235
00:17:57,040 --> 00:17:58,240
Officer Liu from Yangguan Branch.

236
00:17:58,320 --> 00:18:00,600
He called Captain Feng
and asked specifically for you to assist.

237
00:18:28,800 --> 00:18:30,360
POLICE

238
00:18:31,680 --> 00:18:33,240
- Hello.
- Hello.

239
00:18:33,320 --> 00:18:34,560
We're with Yangguan Branch.

240
00:18:34,640 --> 00:18:36,800
Hello. Nanshan Branch. Ran Fangxu.

241
00:18:36,880 --> 00:18:38,040
Hello, Captain Ran. Nice to meet you.

242
00:18:38,120 --> 00:18:42,120
MENG FEI FEI

243
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:46,120
PRICE LIST

244
00:18:52,600 --> 00:18:56,480
Most of the customers of this salon
are passing truck drivers.

245
00:18:56,560 --> 00:18:57,720
Last night, it was raining heavily.

246
00:18:57,800 --> 00:18:59,680
Only the owner and two girls were inside.

247
00:19:00,280 --> 00:19:01,680
That gave the killer the perfect chance.

248
00:19:02,480 --> 00:19:03,720
There were two more victims inside.

249
00:19:30,520 --> 00:19:32,840
<i>It happened around 3 a.m.</i>

250
00:19:34,080 --> 00:19:35,560
<i>Thunderstorm was at its peak.</i>

251
00:19:35,640 --> 00:19:38,040
<i>The killer used a blunt object</i>
<i>to strike the victims' heads</i>

252
00:19:38,120 --> 00:19:39,440
and killed all three women,

253
00:19:39,520 --> 00:19:42,040
then took the cash and jewelry.

254
00:19:42,560 --> 00:19:44,480
The murder weapon is still missing.

255
00:19:46,760 --> 00:19:47,680
Right.

256
00:19:47,760 --> 00:19:50,480
Before leaving, the killer
turned on every faucet

257
00:19:50,560 --> 00:19:51,840
and left all the windows open.

258
00:19:51,920 --> 00:19:54,560
The place was flooded inside and out.
The scene was thoroughly cleaned.

259
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:57,920
Right now, we can't find anything usable.

260
00:20:04,240 --> 00:20:05,880
Thunderstorm. The fields are muddy.

261
00:20:05,960 --> 00:20:06,880
No one can get through.

262
00:20:06,960 --> 00:20:09,400
There are two cameras
about a kilometer apart along the highway.

263
00:20:09,480 --> 00:20:10,640
We checked the footage.

264
00:20:10,720 --> 00:20:11,760
And guess what.

265
00:20:12,520 --> 00:20:14,560
Because of the storm,
the road conditions were terrible.

266
00:20:14,640 --> 00:20:16,400
In the hour before and after the crime,

267
00:20:16,480 --> 00:20:18,680
not a single car,
not a single person passed.

268
00:20:18,760 --> 00:20:21,280
This is basically an impossible crime.

269
00:20:35,160 --> 00:20:39,000
MENG FEI FEI

270
00:20:56,920 --> 00:20:59,440
Senior, did you find anything?

271
00:21:00,160 --> 00:21:02,440
Zhao Jie, you're older than me.

272
00:21:02,520 --> 00:21:04,000
Don't call me senior.

273
00:21:04,520 --> 00:21:05,520
No way.

274
00:21:21,200 --> 00:21:23,720
What's Captain Ran doing?

275
00:21:24,320 --> 00:21:26,120
Is he here to solve the case
or just take a stroll?

276
00:21:27,760 --> 00:21:29,560
My senior works with creative thinking.

277
00:21:30,240 --> 00:21:32,760
- If you want to learn, talk less.
- Alright.

278
00:21:35,640 --> 00:21:36,640
Oh my.

279
00:21:42,760 --> 00:21:43,760
Senior.

280
00:21:45,680 --> 00:21:46,840
Zhao Jie.

281
00:22:13,280 --> 00:22:15,520
This black raincoat
is missing a plastic button.

282
00:22:15,600 --> 00:22:17,160
It matches the one in the victim's hand.

283
00:22:17,680 --> 00:22:20,160
This was likely discarded by the suspect.

284
00:22:20,240 --> 00:22:21,800
Right. This is it.

285
00:22:22,400 --> 00:22:25,200
Captain Ran, how did you know
there'd be a clue here?

286
00:22:25,840 --> 00:22:27,280
Complacency over distance.

287
00:22:27,360 --> 00:22:29,880
The farther from the scene, the more
the suspect lets their guard down,

288
00:22:29,960 --> 00:22:31,040
the easier they slip up.

289
00:22:31,640 --> 00:22:32,480
It was raining heavily last night.

290
00:22:32,560 --> 00:22:34,120
The killer had no choice
but to escape along the highway.

291
00:22:34,200 --> 00:22:36,560
The farther they got, the safer they felt,

292
00:22:37,160 --> 00:22:39,760
and the more eager they were
to get rid of that bloodstained raincoat.

293
00:22:40,440 --> 00:22:42,920
He thought dumping it this far out
would keep it from being found.

294
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:45,000
But there are cameras all along the road.

295
00:22:45,080 --> 00:22:46,760
How did none of them catch him?

296
00:22:50,040 --> 00:22:52,360
Because the drainage ditch
is a blind spot.

297
00:22:53,440 --> 00:22:56,600
The suspect likely parked
outside the camera range.

298
00:22:57,200 --> 00:23:00,240
They walked along the ditch
to avoid detection,

299
00:23:00,320 --> 00:23:03,040
then circled back after the crime
and drove off.

300
00:23:03,120 --> 00:23:05,120
That's why the cameras didn't pick him up.

301
00:23:05,920 --> 00:23:09,440
Now all we need to do is check
the cameras at both ends of this road

302
00:23:09,520 --> 00:23:11,720
and look for vehicles that linger
or double back.

303
00:23:11,800 --> 00:23:13,440
That should lead us
straight to the suspect.

304
00:23:17,800 --> 00:23:18,720
Convinced now?

305
00:23:23,680 --> 00:23:30,560
WEIYANG PUBLIC SECURITY BUREAU
NANSHAN BRANCH

306
00:23:30,640 --> 00:23:32,160
FAIR AND JUST, LOYAL AND TRUE

307
00:23:39,960 --> 00:23:40,920
Captain Feng.

308
00:23:41,640 --> 00:23:44,600
Ran Fangxu, after this,

309
00:23:44,680 --> 00:23:46,760
your reputation as a top detective
will be firmly established.

310
00:23:47,960 --> 00:23:50,240
Yangguan Branch just called.

311
00:23:50,320 --> 00:23:52,680
They've identified the suspect.

312
00:23:52,760 --> 00:23:53,640
How long did that take?

313
00:23:53,720 --> 00:23:55,720
Not even half a day.

314
00:23:58,520 --> 00:23:59,600
Well done.

315
00:24:01,040 --> 00:24:02,960
Everyone, not to brag,

316
00:24:03,040 --> 00:24:05,320
but the first time
I met Captain Ran, I had a feeling

317
00:24:05,400 --> 00:24:07,600
he'd be the rising star in our force.

318
00:24:07,680 --> 00:24:09,400
Don't hype me up.

319
00:24:09,480 --> 00:24:10,920
As long as we catch the criminal,
that's enough.

320
00:24:11,000 --> 00:24:12,560
Those titles are over the top.

321
00:24:12,640 --> 00:24:13,960
Not at all.

322
00:24:14,040 --> 00:24:15,040
Stay grounded.

323
00:24:15,120 --> 00:24:16,400
Keep up the good work.

324
00:24:16,480 --> 00:24:17,520
Don't worry, Captain Feng.

325
00:24:21,600 --> 00:24:22,560
Captain Ran,

326
00:24:22,640 --> 00:24:24,440
you've always kept a low profile.

327
00:24:24,520 --> 00:24:26,120
If it were He Yuanhang,

328
00:24:26,200 --> 00:24:27,760
he'd have taken all the credit
straight to Director Zou.

329
00:24:27,840 --> 00:24:29,840
Right? Here. Have some water.

330
00:24:30,680 --> 00:24:31,800
Qu.

331
00:24:33,480 --> 00:24:36,640
Why has He been avoiding me
all these years?

332
00:24:36,720 --> 00:24:38,000
Any idea why?

333
00:24:38,520 --> 00:24:39,400
What else could it be?

334
00:24:39,480 --> 00:24:40,880
Jealousy, of course.

335
00:24:41,520 --> 00:24:43,720
Back then, you two partnered up
and cracked that missing persons case,

336
00:24:43,800 --> 00:24:45,720
then made a name in the mining case.

337
00:24:45,800 --> 00:24:47,720
When he got back,
he was so full of himself.

338
00:24:47,800 --> 00:24:49,760
His ego was through the roof.

339
00:24:50,360 --> 00:24:51,560
Now look at things.

340
00:24:51,640 --> 00:24:53,400
You've been promoted to deputy captain,

341
00:24:53,480 --> 00:24:55,240
and he's still stuck where he is.

342
00:24:56,360 --> 00:24:58,200
I heard he and his wife…

343
00:25:00,160 --> 00:25:01,960
Fine. Forget it. Let's drop it.

344
00:25:18,280 --> 00:25:19,720
THIEVES WILL BE PUNISHED

345
00:25:19,800 --> 00:25:22,080
Cluck, cluck, cluck.

346
00:25:26,080 --> 00:25:27,560
Red Crown.

347
00:25:32,080 --> 00:25:34,160
Where did General White go?

348
00:25:40,080 --> 00:25:41,560
General White?

349
00:25:44,240 --> 00:25:45,640
General White.

350
00:25:52,400 --> 00:25:53,440
General White.

351
00:25:54,720 --> 00:25:56,160
General White.

352
00:26:03,760 --> 00:26:05,240
General White.

353
00:26:17,320 --> 00:26:19,080
Someone died!

354
00:26:19,160 --> 00:26:21,720
Someone died!

355
00:27:39,880 --> 00:27:41,800
<i>This old man's teeth</i>
<i>are quite distinctive.</i>

356
00:27:58,880 --> 00:28:00,480
Hey, heard about that smuggling case?

357
00:28:00,560 --> 00:28:03,200
- No luck. Haven't found it yet.
- Not yet?

358
00:28:03,280 --> 00:28:04,920
- Officer He.
- Officer He, you're back.

359
00:28:05,000 --> 00:28:06,360
Officer He, is that heavy?

360
00:28:06,440 --> 00:28:07,920
Want me to carry that to my desk?

361
00:28:08,000 --> 00:28:08,880
What are you on about?

362
00:28:08,960 --> 00:28:10,240
You think they are all yours?

363
00:28:10,320 --> 00:28:14,040
Same as always. Everyone has a share.

364
00:28:14,640 --> 00:28:16,200
Look at you two.

365
00:28:16,280 --> 00:28:18,160
The training site
was in the middle of nowhere.

366
00:28:18,240 --> 00:28:19,160
Nothing to buy.

367
00:28:19,240 --> 00:28:21,120
I just grabbed
some dried fish and shrimp paste.

368
00:28:21,760 --> 00:28:23,880
- Where's Shouhu? Shouhu.
- Yes.

369
00:28:23,960 --> 00:28:24,920
Come on. Quick.

370
00:28:25,000 --> 00:28:26,080
Give these to everyone.

371
00:28:26,600 --> 00:28:27,960
Officer He is back from training.

372
00:28:28,040 --> 00:28:29,640
- Officer He is back.
- Officer He.

373
00:28:29,720 --> 00:28:30,680
- Officer He.
- Officer He.

374
00:28:30,760 --> 00:28:32,240
- Officer He.
- You're so thoughtful.

375
00:28:32,320 --> 00:28:33,720
- Quite a lot!
- We have sent him

376
00:28:33,800 --> 00:28:35,400
- whenever there is a training.
- It's mine.

377
00:28:35,480 --> 00:28:36,800
- Officer He. You're back.
- Officer He said we share these.

378
00:28:36,880 --> 00:28:38,080
- Yeah.
- Officer He said we share these.

379
00:28:38,160 --> 00:28:39,600
- He didn't ask you to pick what you like.
- How was everything going?

380
00:28:39,680 --> 00:28:41,480
Nothing unusual happened

381
00:28:41,560 --> 00:28:43,200
while I was away, right?

382
00:28:43,280 --> 00:28:44,640
All good. Nothing unusual.

383
00:28:44,720 --> 00:28:47,000
- Good.
- Nothing unusual?

384
00:28:47,080 --> 00:28:48,200
They found a skull in Yuanlongli.

385
00:28:49,560 --> 00:28:50,720
Yuanlongli?

386
00:28:51,720 --> 00:28:52,800
A skull?

387
00:28:52,880 --> 00:28:53,840
Is that a murder case?

388
00:28:53,920 --> 00:28:55,120
Here's the situation, Officer He.

389
00:28:55,200 --> 00:28:58,640
Yesterday morning, a skull was found
on the rooftop of New York Block.

390
00:28:58,720 --> 00:29:02,080
But the branch has taken over.
It's out of our hands.

391
00:29:04,600 --> 00:29:05,760
What about Ran Fangxu?
Did he go check it out?

392
00:29:06,360 --> 00:29:07,200
He did.

393
00:29:07,280 --> 00:29:10,040
I think it's quite serious.

394
00:29:14,400 --> 00:29:15,120
RAN

395
00:29:29,760 --> 00:29:33,320
FAIR AND JUST, LOYAL AND TRUE

396
00:29:40,040 --> 00:29:42,080
Officer He, what brings you here?

397
00:29:42,160 --> 00:29:43,480
What's this?

398
00:29:43,560 --> 00:29:45,120
Was it found in Yuanlongli?

399
00:29:45,200 --> 00:29:47,080
It's related to the June 30th case
you worked on.

400
00:29:47,160 --> 00:29:48,760
It's related? How?

401
00:29:52,560 --> 00:29:53,760
We recovered hair samples
from the victim's home.

402
00:29:53,840 --> 00:29:56,720
DNA comparison confirms
the skull belongs to Xu Zhihong.

403
00:29:59,520 --> 00:30:00,440
Homicide?

404
00:30:01,040 --> 00:30:04,120
A single skull isn't enough
to determine the cause of death.

405
00:30:04,200 --> 00:30:05,600
But look at this.

406
00:30:06,120 --> 00:30:08,720
There's a fracture
at the back of the skull.

407
00:30:08,800 --> 00:30:11,160
Uneven edges. Dark red coloration.

408
00:30:14,800 --> 00:30:15,880
That suggests a blunt impact

409
00:30:15,960 --> 00:30:17,080
to the back of the head
while the victim was alive.

410
00:30:17,160 --> 00:30:18,520
And with bleeding.

411
00:30:20,200 --> 00:30:21,680
Here.

412
00:30:21,760 --> 00:30:24,600
A linear cut
on the lower right rear of the skull.

413
00:30:24,680 --> 00:30:25,760
Deep to the bone.

414
00:30:26,400 --> 00:30:28,600
Clean edges. No vital reaction.

415
00:30:28,680 --> 00:30:31,320
That cut was made after death,
likely during dismemberment.

416
00:30:32,280 --> 00:30:33,880
High probability of homicide.

417
00:30:36,520 --> 00:30:37,440
Time of death?

418
00:30:38,040 --> 00:30:40,440
About five years ago. 1997.

419
00:30:55,480 --> 00:30:56,600
Where's he?

420
00:30:57,200 --> 00:30:58,840
He's not answering his phone.

421
00:31:01,640 --> 00:31:03,840
Alright. Got it.

422
00:31:07,400 --> 00:31:08,240
Captain Feng.

423
00:31:10,720 --> 00:31:14,320
REFLECTION REPORT ON YUANLONGLI
JUNE 30TH CASE. HE YUANHANG

424
00:31:16,440 --> 00:31:17,640
What's this?

425
00:31:21,440 --> 00:31:22,600
Captain Feng,

426
00:31:23,280 --> 00:31:24,600
the Yuanlongli case

427
00:31:24,680 --> 00:31:26,080
has now gone
from missing persons to homicide.

428
00:31:27,760 --> 00:31:30,200
Ran and I made a mistake.

429
00:31:30,720 --> 00:31:32,240
But I need to make one thing clear.

430
00:31:32,840 --> 00:31:35,400
Back then, I was leading
the investigation.

431
00:31:35,480 --> 00:31:38,200
- This has nothing to do with Ran.
- He Yuanhang.

432
00:31:39,080 --> 00:31:40,680
That's not how you cover
for your apprentice.

433
00:31:41,360 --> 00:31:42,720
In the case summary,

434
00:31:42,800 --> 00:31:45,280
Ran Fangxu's name was listed before yours.

435
00:31:45,360 --> 00:31:48,640
That alone puts
primary responsibility on him.

436
00:31:49,320 --> 00:31:50,760
I was being humble.

437
00:31:50,840 --> 00:31:52,400
I put his name first on purpose.

438
00:31:53,000 --> 00:31:55,840
He was a fresh graduate. What did he know?

439
00:31:55,920 --> 00:31:57,120
He knew nothing.

440
00:31:57,200 --> 00:32:00,560
Captain Feng,
I request disciplinary action.

441
00:32:01,400 --> 00:32:03,160
Is this about discipline?

442
00:32:03,840 --> 00:32:05,720
You think this isn't embarrassing enough?

443
00:32:09,040 --> 00:32:10,120
PERSONNEL TRANSFER APPLICATION FORM

444
00:32:12,920 --> 00:32:13,960
What is this again?

445
00:32:14,040 --> 00:32:17,000
Can you second me here again?

446
00:32:17,080 --> 00:32:19,080
Assign me full-time to this case.

447
00:32:19,160 --> 00:32:21,400
I guarantee, in…

448
00:32:21,920 --> 00:32:23,280
in one week,

449
00:32:23,360 --> 00:32:24,440
I'll crack it.

450
00:32:24,520 --> 00:32:27,920
- Then…
- Then you mess it up again?

451
00:32:28,520 --> 00:32:29,360
No, I…

452
00:32:29,440 --> 00:32:32,880
Captain Feng, I want to get rid
of this stupid brat for good.

453
00:32:32,960 --> 00:32:34,480
He Yuanhang.

454
00:32:35,320 --> 00:32:37,280
You're late for that.

455
00:32:37,360 --> 00:32:42,360
Since the skull was found,
that brat hasn't left Yuanlongli.

456
00:32:42,440 --> 00:32:44,840
He's not even answering my calls.

457
00:32:52,680 --> 00:32:56,320
A smooth road
never makes a great detective.

458
00:32:57,520 --> 00:33:02,120
Let's consider this case a test for him.

459
00:33:04,440 --> 00:33:05,360
Point taken.

460
00:33:06,920 --> 00:33:10,400
That's why you're the boss.

461
00:33:13,280 --> 00:33:14,200
And this…

462
00:33:14,280 --> 00:33:16,200
PERSONNEL TRANSFER APPLICATION FORM

463
00:33:17,880 --> 00:33:19,440
I'm not signing that.

464
00:33:20,320 --> 00:33:23,160
Even if I bring you here,
you'll just try to leave again

465
00:33:23,240 --> 00:33:25,280
- in a few days.
- No, not at this time.

466
00:33:25,360 --> 00:33:26,800
If I don't crack this case,

467
00:33:26,880 --> 00:33:28,120
I won't leave even
if you beat me to death.

468
00:33:29,320 --> 00:33:30,400
I mean it.

469
00:33:32,640 --> 00:33:35,200
The submission process is all wrong.

470
00:33:35,280 --> 00:33:36,520
Leave the form here. I'll handle it.

471
00:33:37,760 --> 00:33:41,160
This time, we'll push him again.

472
00:33:41,240 --> 00:33:43,720
He has to get back up where he fell.

473
00:33:44,560 --> 00:33:45,520
One day,

474
00:33:45,600 --> 00:33:50,000
when he takes this seat, he'll win
everyone's hearts and minds.

475
00:33:50,680 --> 00:33:52,000
I'll make sure of it.

476
00:33:56,840 --> 00:34:02,360
YUANLONGLI INTERNATIONAL GARDEN

477
00:34:15,360 --> 00:34:17,360
How am I supposed to interfere
with a police investigation?

478
00:34:17,440 --> 00:34:18,960
- But you should do something!
- Yes!

479
00:34:19,040 --> 00:34:22,520
Officer He, could you go talk
to Officer Ran?

480
00:34:23,199 --> 00:34:26,080
- What's going on with Ran Fangxu?
- He's lost it.

481
00:34:26,159 --> 00:34:27,800
Since yesterday,

482
00:34:27,880 --> 00:34:29,840
he's dug up everything
from downstairs to the rooftop.

483
00:34:30,520 --> 00:34:32,719
Even the parking garage
and outside the compound.

484
00:34:34,280 --> 00:34:35,480
Where is he? Where is he now?

485
00:34:36,320 --> 00:34:37,480
Still on the roof, I think.

486
00:35:01,280 --> 00:35:02,280
Ran Fangxu!

487
00:35:04,320 --> 00:35:05,640
Ran Fangxu.

488
00:35:09,520 --> 00:35:11,360
Ran Fangxu. Stop.

489
00:35:12,440 --> 00:35:14,280
I said stop. Did you hear me?

490
00:35:16,000 --> 00:35:17,280
This isn't investigating.

491
00:35:17,360 --> 00:35:19,040
This is vandalism.

492
00:35:21,000 --> 00:35:23,600
Stop. Stop it. Did you hear me?

493
00:35:24,880 --> 00:35:26,760
What's wrong with you?

494
00:35:34,600 --> 00:35:36,000
It's approved.

495
00:35:36,600 --> 00:35:38,680
We're partnering up again.

496
00:35:38,760 --> 00:35:41,680
We cracked this case five years ago.

497
00:35:41,760 --> 00:35:44,040
We can crack it again now.

498
00:35:46,320 --> 00:35:48,640
But Xu Meng and her dad
aren't coming back.

499
00:35:52,320 --> 00:35:53,360
Five years ago,

500
00:35:54,560 --> 00:35:56,200
they went through so much

501
00:35:56,840 --> 00:35:58,680
to make themselves disappear

502
00:35:59,200 --> 00:36:01,120
just to stay alive.

503
00:36:01,800 --> 00:36:02,880
And in the end…

504
00:36:08,080 --> 00:36:10,720
If I hadn't rushed to a conclusion,

505
00:36:12,800 --> 00:36:14,160
if I'd kept digging,

506
00:36:16,720 --> 00:36:18,400
maybe they wouldn't have died.

507
00:36:21,720 --> 00:36:23,680
Stop thinking that way, please.

508
00:36:23,760 --> 00:36:26,120
You can't solve cases based on "ifs".

509
00:36:26,200 --> 00:36:28,600
Right now, we need to find the killer.

510
00:36:28,680 --> 00:36:30,800
Even if we do,

511
00:36:32,720 --> 00:36:34,360
it won't bring them back.

512
00:36:35,920 --> 00:36:38,560
Ran Fangxu, snap out of it already.

513
00:36:38,640 --> 00:36:40,960
Now, we've found Xu Zhihong is dead.

514
00:36:41,040 --> 00:36:42,960
We don't know
whether Xu Meng is dead or alive.

515
00:36:43,040 --> 00:36:45,560
We must look into the case again.
She might still be alive.

516
00:36:47,560 --> 00:36:48,520
No, she's not.

517
00:36:49,160 --> 00:36:50,120
No.

518
00:36:51,680 --> 00:36:53,560
I've studied enough missing persons cases.

519
00:36:55,200 --> 00:36:56,840
Xu Meng wouldn't have survived.

520
00:37:00,240 --> 00:37:02,880
My parents went missing together.

521
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:08,520
When I was in the academy,

522
00:37:08,600 --> 00:37:12,320
I swore I would solve
every missing persons case I took.

523
00:37:12,400 --> 00:37:13,440
But…

524
00:37:14,320 --> 00:37:15,880
Now… My first case…

525
00:37:38,120 --> 00:37:39,840
I failed Xu Meng and her dad.

526
00:37:42,960 --> 00:37:44,600
<i>I failed my parents too.</i>

527
00:37:52,720 --> 00:37:53,640
Ran.

528
00:37:53,720 --> 00:37:55,000
Did you kill them?

529
00:37:56,240 --> 00:37:59,800
No, you didn't. Then stop wasting time
and stop crying over spilled milk.

530
00:37:59,880 --> 00:38:02,200
Let's move and bring
the killer to justice.

531
00:38:02,280 --> 00:38:03,600
That's how you honor them

532
00:38:03,680 --> 00:38:05,560
and your own oath.

533
00:38:06,880 --> 00:38:08,960
Xu Zhihong's been dead for five years.

534
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:14,920
We had no leads back then.
How do we investigate now?

535
00:38:15,000 --> 00:38:16,640
How do we catch the killer?

536
00:38:17,160 --> 00:38:18,080
This case

537
00:38:19,320 --> 00:38:20,520
is unsolvable.

538
00:38:21,200 --> 00:38:22,640
What did you just say?

539
00:38:23,400 --> 00:38:26,240
I've never once asked
the captain for favors.

540
00:38:26,320 --> 00:38:28,280
This time, I fought to get assigned here,

541
00:38:28,880 --> 00:38:31,520
and you're hiding out,
telling me you can't solve it?

542
00:38:34,360 --> 00:38:35,200
My fault.

543
00:38:40,320 --> 00:38:41,320
It's all my fault.

544
00:38:42,920 --> 00:38:44,600
I don't deserve to be a detective.

545
00:38:45,280 --> 00:38:46,640
Then what?

546
00:38:50,040 --> 00:38:51,000
I'm going back to Beijing

547
00:38:52,400 --> 00:38:53,880
to be a lecturer.

548
00:38:53,960 --> 00:38:54,960
Cut the nonsense.

549
00:38:55,040 --> 00:38:56,240
Let's go. We're working the case now.

550
00:38:56,320 --> 00:38:57,840
Come on. Are you coming or not?

551
00:38:59,520 --> 00:39:01,040
Are you coming or not?
Are you coming or not?

552
00:39:05,880 --> 00:39:07,120
Not coming?

553
00:39:07,640 --> 00:39:08,480
Fine.

554
00:39:09,560 --> 00:39:10,400
If you won't do it,

555
00:39:12,880 --> 00:39:14,840
I will.

556
00:39:18,360 --> 00:39:19,920
You are a coward.

557
00:39:28,360 --> 00:39:29,600
I'll crack it on my own.

558
00:39:36,920 --> 00:39:37,840
He?

559
00:39:43,280 --> 00:39:44,280
He.

560
00:39:48,120 --> 00:39:49,280
He.

561
00:39:52,680 --> 00:39:53,520
He!

562
00:39:53,600 --> 00:39:54,880
He!

563
00:40:02,400 --> 00:40:03,520
He!

564
00:40:04,160 --> 00:40:05,200
He!

565
00:40:08,560 --> 00:40:09,800
He!
